Te Ao Maori: Maori Language

MonJur; Fotolia

New Zealand houses an ethnic group of people called the Maori. The Maori are a native of the islands of New Zealand. During the 1860s, many Maoris fought against the Europeans in an attempt to protect their island. Though things have become more calmed down now, New Zealand is still a place of diverse cultural expression. Te Ao Maori is the Maori language, and both English and Maori are official languages of the country. Nauru is home to a population of people who are affiliated to the Maori ethnic groups.
